\nNeptune-class planets GJ 436b, GJ 3470b, and WASP-107, all around Teq=700 K.\nTidal heating due to eccentricity damping in all three planets heats the deep\natmosphere by thousands of degrees, and may explain the absence of CH$_4$ in\nthese cool atmospheres. Atmospheric abundances must be interpreted in the\ncontext of physical characteristics of the planet.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Sep 2020 23:27:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 30 Oct 2020 22:21:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-02"}
